# Git workflow — at-hand reference

Full contract: `AGENTS.md` → *Branching, commits, PRs*.

- **Never** push to `main`, force-push, disable branch
  protection, or pass `--no-verify`.
- Branch: `<type>/<short-kebab-subject>` (e.g. `feat/trail-filter`).
- Commit subject matches
  `^(build|chore|ci|docs|feat|fix|perf|refactor|revert|style|test)(\([a-z0-9._-]+\))?!?: .{1,100}$`
  and carries the trailer
  `Co-authored-by: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>`.
- One logical change per commit. One user-visible change per PR.
- PR body uses plain `-` bullets only. **Never** `- [ ]` / `- [x]` —
  unticked boxes freeze the merged PR at `X of Y tasks` forever.
- Run the project's lint / typecheck / test commands (see
  `docs/knowledge.md` → Architecture) before opening a PR.
- Dependencies: one package manager per project; commit lockfiles;
  never hand-edit them. Defaults in
  `.gaia/reference/preferences.md`.
- On a fresh clone, `scripts/setup-hooks.sh` wires the commit
  template and hooks path.
